{"type":"message","id":"e948619e","parentId":"35e6ccac","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:06:41.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usually, in common size scales (`xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`), **`xs` is the smallest predefined one**.\n\nBut in some systems/frameworks, there can be sizes below it, such as:\n\n- `2xs` / `xxs` (extra-extra-small)\n- `3xs` (in a few design systems, e.g. spacing/text scales)\n\nSo the short answer: **yes, sometimes — but it depends on the design system/library you’re using.**  \nIf you tell me the specific one (Tailwind, MUI, Chakra, Bootstrap, etc.), I can give the exact size options.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f7ee52d1f022d230169e0d0ce780c8191b92a224866fed2b6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":4003,"output":140,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4143,"cost":{"input":0.00700525,"output":0.00196,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008965250000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341197664,"responseId":"resp_0f7ee52d1f022d230169e0d0cdfb9081919203e698089a72a5"}}
